.TH "devm_spi_register_controller" 9 "devm_spi_register_controller" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_spi_register_controller \- register managed SPI master or slave controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_spi_register_controller
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct spi_controller *ctlr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device managing SPI controller
.IP "ctlr" 12
initialized controller, originally from \fBspi_alloc_master\fP or
\fBspi_alloc_slave\fP
.SH "CONTEXT"
can sleep
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Register a SPI device as with \fBspi_register_controller\fP which will
automatically be unregistered and freed.
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success, else a negative error code.
